review:
In 2019, I currently have 3 smartphones and 2 AI 'Home Assistants' in my home. Also, a company I do business with has switched to online customer service 'chat' with bots. I remember the first time I found myself going round-and-round over the same issues with this 'person', when I realized it was a bot. I tested it by asking for a human being, and it kept saying, "I couldn't understand your request..." I started typing "HUMAN! HUMAN! HUMAN! HUMAN!" Of coarse, the bot didn't have an intelligent response to my unintelligent angry rant... not yet, anyway.<br/><br/>In the past, it was sometimes irritating not having a human to help us out and having to settle for 'dumb AI'. In the future, we may wish we could go back to the days of 'dumb AI'.<br/><br/>RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
